A South East-based socio-cultural organization, The Eastern Conscience, has pleaded with President Muhammadu Buhari to sign the South East Development Bill now. The group described the bill as a landmark and a gesture of goodwill for the people of the region. In a statement signed by the convener, Evang. Myke Ikoku, the group said, “We wish to commend Mr. President for the South-East Development Commission Bill which is on his table. As far as the South-East geopolitical zone is concerned, when this bill is assented to, it will represent a historic and landmark gesture to the entire Igbo nation.” OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE The group also implored the president to ignore any protest against his Chief of Staff, Abba Kyari and his kinsman, Mammam Daura. Ikoku said the protest was misdirected because the duo had sacrificed a lot for the president. Senate passes bill to establish Southeast devt commission Biafra agitation can scuttle Igbo presidency - APC Protests as FG reverts Alvan Ikoku varsity to COE Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin